I see a friend this week who has a teen sister with skin problems and you bet I am sharing not just any "dead sea mud mask" but this brand specifically.I truly am impressed with the results.I have had professional facials and this does feel as soothing, refreshing and has astounding results.In the past other masks I have tried never felt as much as a at home luxury as this one does.Plus the benefits are numerous. It does not dry our your skin. I felt nicely moisturized, in the most natural way. I did not feel any artificial residue or anything like that.I don't know what, more I can say. I hope my long review was helpful. I wanted to add as much as possible so it covered it all.How fast acting it was. It's soothing effects. Natural moisture. Swelling reduction. The cystic acne cleared up considerably faster. Black heads gone completely unlike other masks. Lovely smell. No drying. No negative reactions on my sensative skin. Smooth skin. Pore refinement.*I Hope to add photos in the future*

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing Mud Mask!
reviews.reviewText: Dead Sea Mud Mask; Pores, Blackheads, Whiteheads, Acne and Breakouts; 100% natural formula to ensure the highest-quality product. Simply unique due to its high concentrations of salts and minerals effective in restoring a healthy rosy glow to the skin; Can be used as Blackhead Remover Mask as well as Acne MaskExcellent for face skin care, deep pore cleansing, detoxifying and revitalization. Works on Oily and sensitive skin as well. Similar to Bentonite Clay, it makes a fabulous facial mask, for shrinking pores, tightening and toning skin, removing impurities, and just making your skin look and feel great.PREMIUM QUALITY THERAPEUTIC GRADE: Dead Sea mud is known to be effective for skin conditions, such as psoriasis and dermatitis, especially when used in conjunction with adjunct therapies, such as Dead Sea bathing, moisturizing creams, and increased sun exposure. It's also useful for relaxing sore muscles. SOOTHING SKIN: Naturally softens and moisturizes, so it dramatically improves the appearance and health of your skin leaving it more tone, even in texture, and clearer.IndicationsDead Sea Mud Mask is commonly used for detoxification, as a facial mask, to improve skin conditions and to help reduce aches and pains. it can also be used for various skin condition such as blackheads or pimples as well as a full body mask. [Important FDA Statement]: These Statements have not been evaluated by the food and drug administration. This product is not intended to diagnose, mitigate, treat, cure or prevent any disease.IngredientsDeionized water, Pure Dead Sea Mud, Kaolin, Shea Butter, Sunflower Oil, Aloe Vera Juice, Vegetable Glycerin, Jojoba Oil, Hickory Bark Extract, Calendula Oil, Xanthan GumDirectionsApply a thick layer on the face and upper part of the neck, avoiding the eye area. Leave on to dry for 5 minutes. Remove the mask first by gently rubbing in circular motions for an overall exfoliation. Wash any excess with lukewarm water and gently pat dry. Recommended to use twice a week and to follow with your favorite moisturizer.I absolutely love this company and how they have a holistic approach to beauty products. I bought this product to help reduce acne, blackheads, and to refine/brighten my skin. It feels cool and refreshing upon application. I let it completely dry for about 20-30 min and wash off with warm water. I try to use it two to three times a week and feel it works very well! I feel and look refreshed! My skin has significantly improved and my pores are gradually getting smaller and are less noticeable. I will be purchasing more in the future and absolutely love it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality, Salt Burns Cuts...Duh?
reviews.reviewText: Great product. Feels great on my super sensitive skin. It left my skin smooth and refreshed after washing off. For all the people saying this product burns it is because 1 of 3 things is causing it: open cut on your face, itritated acne, you shave or waxed your face. The product has salt in it. Salt burns irritated areas on your face (feels like going into ocean after shaving your legs). For all the people saying they got acne from this product, its because: you didn't wash the product off completely with warm water OR this product opens up your pores very well and causes debris to come into the pores easier. Wash your face with water and moisturize with a light weight oil free moisturizer.

This is unlike a clay mask which I can brush on. This product is like jello. So instead of using a brush or fingers to pat on treat this like a bar of soap. Add a dollop in the palm of your hands, rub together to warm it up and thin it down. Massage all over your face.After a few minutes you will begin to feel a slight warm sensation. Wash off with a very damp facecloth. ( and use a crappy cloth). Your skin will look amazing after it is all washed off.

No puedo calificar el producto puesto que me fue robado del lugar de entrega.Estoy segura que por la descripción del producto en el momento de la compra debería haber tenido una buena puntuación. Un saludo.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 2, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: Soft, bright and cleansing! Would recommend!
reviews.reviewText: Bought this product due to great reviews. Just used it for the first time and my face feels so soft. The product goes on so nicely and feels silky to the touch. It doesn't dry and tighten your face like many mud face packs you can get in chemists. I left the face mask on for 10-15 mins and washed off with warm water. My face now feels as soft as a baby's bum and looks clean and bright. I noticed some light reflecting particles that had been left on my skin, which I wasn't expecting, which adds extra glow! Very nice product, look forward to continued use.
